data.description: ***Offering $5,000 in Closing Cost with reasonable offer***  Welcome Home to this charming bungalow in Historic Downtown Camden. This home features five bedrooms, four baths, formal living and dining areas. The owner's suite is a true getaway with a sitting area overlooking one of the beautiful fireplaces, office, and en-suite bath boasting double vanity and oversized spa shower.  The newly designed walk-in closet has more than enough room for all of your items.  The kitchen has granite countertops, stainless steel appliances and eat-in area. The mudroom leading out to the back deck has built-ins for all things. Upstairs you will find the remaining four bedrooms and two full baths. Tall ceilings and beautiful heart pine floors are throughout most of the home.  A detached two-car garage with a workshop and large finished room to entertain all of your guest is located just out the back door. Spend numerous evenings in the fully fenced-in backyard, grilling on the back deck with your friends and family.  Swing on the shady front porch, on one of Camden's most desired streets that is walking distance to parks, schools, and churches. With a central location, enjoy all of the shopping, entertainment and dining that downtown Camden has to offer. 2020 new tankless water heater, 2020 enclosed laundry/mud room added hvac, 2023 updated owners closet, renovated full bath on first floor & jack and jill bath on 2nd floor, 2023 refrigerator.
